properties.name: fhirFamilyMemberHistory
properties.documentation: Significant health conditions for a person related to the patient relevant in the context of care for the patient.

properties.name: resourceType
properties.documentation: This is a FamilyMemberHistory resource

properties.name: id
properties.documentation: The logical id of the resource, as used in the URL for the resource. Once assigned, this value never changes.

properties.name: meta
properties.documentation: The metadata about the resource. This is content that is maintained by the infrastructure. Changes to the content might not always be associated with version changes to the resource.

properties.name: implicitRules
properties.documentation: A reference to a set of rules that were followed when the resource was constructed, and which must be understood when processing the content. Often, this is a reference to an implementation guide that defines the special rules along with other profiles etc.

properties.name: language
properties.documentation: The base language in which the resource is written.

properties.name: text
properties.documentation: A human-readable narrative that contains a summary of the resource and can be used to represent the content of the resource to a human. The narrative need not encode all the structured data, but is required to contain sufficient detail to make it "clinically safe" for a human to just read the narrative. Resource definitions may define what content should be represented in the narrative to ensure clinical safety.

properties.name: contained
properties.documentation: These resources do not have an independent existence apart from the resource that contains them - they cannot be identified independently, and nor can they have their own independent transaction scope.

properties.name: identifier
properties.documentation: Business identifiers assigned to this family member history by the performer or other systems which remain constant as the resource is updated and propagates from server to server.

properties.name: instantiatesCanonical
properties.documentation: The URL pointing to a FHIR-defined protocol, guideline, orderset or other definition that is adhered to in whole or in part by this FamilyMemberHistory.

properties.name: instantiatesUri
properties.documentation: The URL pointing to an externally maintained protocol, guideline, orderset or other definition that is adhered to in whole or in part by this FamilyMemberHistory.

properties.name: status
properties.documentation: A code specifying the status of the record of the family history of a specific family member.

properties.name: dataAbsentReason
properties.documentation: Describes why the family member's history is not available.

properties.name: patient
properties.documentation: The person who this history concerns.

properties.name: date
properties.documentation: The date (and possibly time) when the family member history was recorded or last updated.

properties.name: name
properties.documentation: This will either be a name or a description; e.g. "Aunt Susan", "my cousin with the red hair".

properties.name: relationship
properties.documentation: The type of relationship this person has to the patient (father, mother, brother etc.).

properties.name: sex
properties.documentation: The birth sex of the family member.

properties.name: bornPeriod
properties.documentation: The actual or approximate date of birth of the relative.

properties.name: bornDate
properties.documentation: The actual or approximate date of birth of the relative.

properties.name: bornString
properties.documentation: The actual or approximate date of birth of the relative.

properties.name: ageAge
properties.documentation: The age of the relative at the time the family member history is recorded.

properties.name: ageRange
properties.documentation: The age of the relative at the time the family member history is recorded.

properties.name: ageString
properties.documentation: The age of the relative at the time the family member history is recorded.

properties.name: estimatedAge
properties.documentation: If true, indicates that the age value specified is an estimated value.

properties.name: deceasedBoolean
properties.documentation: Deceased flag or the actual or approximate age of the relative at the time of death for the family member history record.

properties.name: deceasedAge
properties.documentation: Deceased flag or the actual or approximate age of the relative at the time of death for the family member history record.

properties.name: deceasedRange
properties.documentation: Deceased flag or the actual or approximate age of the relative at the time of death for the family member history record.

properties.name: deceasedDate
properties.documentation: Deceased flag or the actual or approximate age of the relative at the time of death for the family member history record.

properties.name: deceasedString
properties.documentation: Deceased flag or the actual or approximate age of the relative at the time of death for the family member history record.

properties.name: reasonCode
properties.documentation: Describes why the family member history occurred in coded or textual form.

properties.name: reasonReference
properties.documentation: Indicates a Condition, Observation, AllergyIntolerance, or QuestionnaireResponse that justifies this family member history event.

properties.name: note
properties.documentation: This property allows a non condition-specific note to the made about the related person. Ideally, the note would be in the condition property, but this is not always possible.

properties.name: condition
properties.documentation: The significant Conditions (or condition) that the family member had. This is a repeating section to allow a system to represent more than one condition per resource, though there is nothing stopping multiple resources - one per condition.

properties.name: fhirMeta
properties.documentation: The metadata about a resource. This is content in the resource that is maintained by the infrastructure. Changes to the content might not always be associated with version changes to the resource.

properties.name: id
properties.documentation: Unique id for the element within a resource (for internal references). This may be any string value that does not contain spaces.

properties.name: versionId
properties.documentation: The version specific identifier, as it appears in the version portion of the URL. This value changes when the resource is created, updated, or deleted.

properties.name: lastUpdated
properties.documentation: When the resource last changed - e.g. when the version changed.

properties.name: source
properties.documentation: A uri that identifies the source system of the resource. This provides a minimal amount of [[[Provenance]]] information that can be used to track or differentiate the source of information in the resource. The source may identify another FHIR server, document, message, database, etc.

properties.name: profile
properties.documentation: A list of profiles (references to [[[StructureDefinition]]] resources) that this resource claims to conform to. The URL is a reference to [[[StructureDefinition.url]]].

properties.name: security
properties.documentation: Security labels applied to this resource. These tags connect specific resources to the overall security policy and infrastructure.

properties.name: tag
properties.documentation: Tags applied to this resource. Tags are intended to be used to identify and relate resources to process and workflow, and applications are not required to consider the tags when interpreting the meaning of a resource.

properties.name: version
properties.documentation: The version of the code system which was used when choosing this code. Note that a well-maintained code system does not need the version reported, because the meaning of codes is consistent across versions. However this cannot consistently be assured, and when the meaning is not guaranteed to be consistent, the version SHOULD be exchanged.

properties.name: code
properties.documentation: A symbol in syntax defined by the system. The symbol may be a predefined code or an expression in a syntax defined by the coding system (e.g. post-coordination).

properties.name: display
properties.documentation: A representation of the meaning of the code in the system, following the rules of the system.

properties.name: userSelected
properties.documentation: Indicates that this coding was chosen by a user directly - e.g. off a pick list of available items (codes or displays).

properties.name: fhirNarrative
properties.documentation: A human-readable summary of the resource conveying the essential clinical and business information for the resource.

properties.name: id
properties.documentation: Unique id for the element within a resource (for internal references). This may be any string value that does not contain spaces.

properties.name: status
properties.documentation: The status of the narrative - whether it's entirely generated (from just the defined data or the extensions too), or whether a human authored it and it may contain additional data.

properties.name: div

properties.name: fhirReference
properties.documentation: A reference from one resource to another.

properties.name: id
properties.documentation: Unique id for the element within a resource (for internal references). This may be any string value that does not contain spaces.

properties.name: reference
properties.documentation: A reference to a location at which the other resource is found. The reference may be a relative reference, in which case it is relative to the service base URL, or an absolute URL that resolves to the location where the resource is found. The reference may be version specific or not. If the reference is not to a FHIR RESTful server, then it should be assumed to be version specific. Internal fragment references (start with '#') refer to contained resources.

properties.name: type
properties.documentation:
The expected type of the target of the reference. If both Reference.type and Reference.reference are populated and Reference.reference is a FHIR URL, both SHALL be consistent.

The type is the Canonical URL of Resource Definition that is the type this reference refers to. References are URLs that are relative to http://hl7.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/ e.g. "Patient" is a reference to http://hl7.org/fhir/StructureDefinition/Patient. Absolute URLs are only allowed for logical models (and can only be used in references in logical models, not resources).

properties.name: identifier
properties.documentation: An identifier for the target resource. This is used when there is no way to reference the other resource directly, either because the entity it represents is not available through a FHIR server, or because there is no way for the author of the resource to convert a known identifier to an actual location. There is no requirement that a Reference.identifier point to something that is actually exposed as a FHIR instance, but it SHALL point to a business concept that would be expected to be exposed as a FHIR instance, and that instance would need to be of a FHIR resource type allowed by the reference.

properties.name: end
properties.documentation: The end of the period. If the end of the period is missing, it means no end was known or planned at the time the instance was created. The start may be in the past, and the end date in the future, which means that period is expected/planned to end at that time.

properties.name: fhirAge

properties.name: fhirFamilyMemberHistory_Condition
properties.documentation: Significant health conditions for a person related to the patient relevant in the context of care for the patient.

properties.name: id
properties.documentation: Unique id for the element within a resource (for internal references). This may be any string value that does not contain spaces.

properties.name: code
properties.documentation: The actual condition specified. Could be a coded condition (like MI or Diabetes) or a less specific string like 'cancer' depending on how much is known about the condition and the capabilities of the creating system.

properties.name: outcome
properties.documentation: Indicates what happened following the condition.  If the condition resulted in death, deceased date is captured on the relation.

properties.name: contributedToDeath
properties.documentation: This condition contributed to the cause of death of the related person. If contributedToDeath is not populated, then it is unknown.

properties.name: onsetAge
properties.documentation: Either the age of onset, range of approximate age or descriptive string can be recorded.  For conditions with multiple occurrences, this describes the first known occurrence.

properties.name: onsetRange
properties.documentation: Either the age of onset, range of approximate age or descriptive string can be recorded.  For conditions with multiple occurrences, this describes the first known occurrence.

properties.name: onsetPeriod
properties.documentation: Either the age of onset, range of approximate age or descriptive string can be recorded.  For conditions with multiple occurrences, this describes the first known occurrence.

properties.name: onsetString
properties.documentation: Either the age of onset, range of approximate age or descriptive string can be recorded.  For conditions with multiple occurrences, this describes the first known occurrence.

properties.name: note
properties.documentation: An area where general notes can be placed about this specific condition.
